  "response": "Cannibals are individuals who engage in cannibalism, which is the practice of consuming the flesh or internal organs of other individuals of the same species. In humans, this practice is extremely rare and often considered taboo, immoral, or illegal in many societies and cultures. The motivations behind cannibalism can vary widely, ranging from survival in extreme circumstances, ritualistic or cultural practices, to psychological disorders. In literature and media, cannibals are often portrayed as villains or used to evoke fear and horror.",
